Package exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DBAppException  
    DBEngineException  
    DeleteFromEmptyTableException
    Thrown when attempting to delete from an empty table.
    DuplicatePrimaryKeyException
    Thrown when attempting to insert a tuple with an existing primary key to preserve the integrity constraints.
    EntryNotFoundException
    Exception for when the user tries to update or delete a non existant entry
    InvalidInsertionException
    Thrown when inserting in a column with a different type than what the schema of the table defines and thus violating the schema.
    InvalidOperatorException
    Exception for when the user uses non supported Operators other than OR or AND
    NonExistantColumnException
    Exception for when the user tries to insert , select or access a non existent table
    NonExistantTableException
    Exception for when the user tries to insert , select or access a non existent table
    NotPrimaryKeyRefrenceException
    Exception for when the user tries to reference a column in the table that isn't the primary key
    TableAlreadyExistsException
    Exception for when the user tries to create an already existent table
    UnsupportedTypeException
    Thrown when attempting to create a table with unsupported data types.
